docs.abstract: Big tech companies are asking themselves where their responsibilities start and stop. Sorting that out will be complicated and may end up increasing their power.
docs.snippet: Big tech companies are asking themselves where their responsibilities start and stop. Sorting that out will be complicated and may end up increasing their power.
docs.lead_paragraph: From its earliest days, Silicon Valley has been animated by near-absolutist understanding of free speech. Other than exceptions for fraud, pornography or specific threats, the prevailing view among many tech platforms has been to allow pretty much anyone to post pretty much anything. These sensibilities are even enshrined in American law, which gives companies broad immunity from prosecution for what their users post.

headline.main: Tech Companies Like Facebook and Twitter Are Drawing Lines. It’ll Be Messy.
headline.print_headline: Big Tech Is Drawing Lines. So Far, Very Fuzzy Ones.
